## 7. Core Functional Requirements\
\
### 7.1 Launch Configuration\
\
1. **Create Launch**\
   - Manual or via Aha sync.\
   - Required: name, product, tier, target date, owner.\
   - On creation, auto-attach active Criteria matching tier and create LaunchCriterionStatus rows with `NOT_SET`.\
\
2. **Edit Launch**\
   - PM/Product Ops can edit tier, target date, owner, notes.\
   - Recompute risk and reminders on change.\
\
3. **Archive / Cancel Launch**\
   - Mark `CANCELLED`; retain historical data.\
\
---\
\
### 7.2 Criteria Configuration (Admin)\
\
- Product Ops can create/edit global Criteria.\
- Criteria grouped by category; `sort_order` controls display.\
- `is_active = false` stops criteria being instantiated for new launches.\
\
---\
\
### 7.3 Launch Readiness Evaluation\
\
#### 7.3.1 Per-Criterion Status\
\
- Decision Owner or Product Ops sets `status` and updates notes.\
- If `CONDITIONAL_GO`:\
  - Must set `condition`, `condition_type`, `condition_due_date`, `condition_owner_id`.\
\
Scoring:\
\
- GO \uc0\u8594  2  \
- CONDITIONAL_GO \uc0\u8594  1  \
- NO_GO \uc0\u8594  0  \
- NOT_SET \uc0\u8594  null  \
\
---\
\
#### 7.3.2 Launch-Level Verdict & Readiness Score\
\
**Readiness Score (0\'961)**\
\
- Consider only non-gate criteria (`gate = false`).\
- `readiness_score = sum(score_value) / (2 * number_of_non_gate_criteria_with_status_set)`.\
\
**Launch Verdict (status)**\
\
- Base: `IN_EVALUATION` if any criterion is set.\
- Rules:\
  - Any gate == `NO_GO` \uc0\u8594  launch.status = `NO_GO`.\
  - Else any gate == `CONDITIONAL_GO` with unresolved pre-launch condition \uc0\u8594  `CONDITIONAL_GO`.\
  - Else tier thresholds:\
    - Tier 1: readiness \uc0\u8805  0.9 \u8594  `GO`, else `CONDITIONAL_GO`.\
    - Tier 2: readiness \uc0\u8805  0.8 \u8594  `GO`, else `CONDITIONAL_GO`.\
    - Tier 3: readiness \uc0\u8805  0.7 \u8594  `GO`, else `CONDITIONAL_GO` (must-have gates cannot be `NO_GO`).\
\
Manual override allowed for Product Ops/CPO with a recorded reason.\
\
**Risk Level**\
\
- `days_to_launch = target_launch_date - today`.\
\
Example:\
\
- `HIGH` if `days_to_launch <= 30` and any gate not GO or readiness below threshold.\
- `MEDIUM` if `days_to_launch <= 60` and readiness moderately below threshold.\
- Else `LOW`.\
\
---\
\
### 7.4 Views & UX\
\
#### 7.4.1 Portfolio Dashboard\
\
- Table of launches with:\
  - Name, Product/Pillar/Pod, Tier, target date, days to launch, status, readiness %, risk, gate counts.\
- Filters: tier, pillar, pod, owner, status, timeframe.\
- Sort: target date, risk, readiness.\
\
#### 7.4.2 Launch Detail View\
\
- Header: launch name, product, tier, dates, status, risk, readiness bar, gate counts.\
- Matrix: criteria grouped by category with status, owners, conditions, timestamps.\
- Action: create DecisionSnapshot (\'93Take Go/No-Go Snapshot\'94).\
\
#### 7.4.3 Owner View (\'93My Items\'94)\
\
- For current user:\
  - All LaunchCriterionStatus where they\'92re decision_owner or condition_owner.\
  - Show launch, product, criterion, status, condition, due date, overdue flag.\
\
#### 7.4.4 Decision Log / Snapshots\
\
- List snapshots for launch:\
  - Decision date/time, type, verdict, notes, creator.\
- Selecting snapshot shows read-only matrix state at that time.\
\
---\
\
### 7.5 Notifications & Alerts (v1)\
\
1. **Stale Criterion Reminder**\
   - If `last_updated_at` older than X days (e.g., 14) and status != GO:\
     - Email reminder to decision_owner.\
\
2. **Upcoming Launch Risk Alert**\
   - Weekly:\
     - Launches with `days_to_launch <= 45` and `risk_level = HIGH`.\
     - Notify launch owner, pod lead, Product Ops.\
\
3. **Weekly Digest (CPO / Product Leads)**\
   - Top N launches by tier, risk, and days-to-launch.\
   - Include status, readiness, key gate blockers.\
\
Channels: email in v1, Slack later.\
\
---\
\
### 7.6 Aha Integration (Summary)\
\
- Aha Epics are the canonical **Launch** source.\
- We:\
  - Read tier, GA date, owner, product/pod, priority, tags, etc.\
  - Write back readiness status, score, risk, Go/No-Go date, and a URL back to the console.\
- A separate technical doc specifies exact field mapping and API details.\
\
---\
\
### 7.7 Permissions & Roles\
\
- All authenticated users: read access to portfolio and launch detail.\
- Launch owner, Product Ops, CPO: edit launch metadata.\
- LaunchCriterionStatus: editable by decision_owner and Product Ops; others read-only.\
- Criteria configuration: Product Ops & CPO only.\
\
---\
\
### 7.8 Audit & Logging\
\
- Log:\
  - Launch.status, tier, target date changes.\
  - LaunchCriterionStatus.status/condition/decision_owner changes.\
  - DecisionSnapshot creation.\
- Store audit entries with timestamp, user, entity type/id, JSON diff.\
\
---\
\
## 8. Non-Functional Requirements\
\
- Portfolio view (\uc0\u8804 100 launches): < 2s.\
- Launch detail (~50 criteria): < 1s after fetch.\
- 99%+ availability (internal tool).\
- SSO, RBAC, HTTPS.\
- No customer PII stored.\
\
Tech stack:\
\
- Frontend: React + TypeScript + Vite + Mantine.\
- Backend: Node/TypeScript or Supabase functions.\
- DB: Postgres (Supabase).\
- Jobs: n8n or backend scheduler.\
\
---\
\
## 9. Analytics & Success Metrics\
\
- Adoption:\
  - Launches in console vs Aha epics tagged as Launch.\
  - % of Tier 1/2 launches using console for Go/No-Go.\
\
- Data Freshness:\
  - Median age of criteria updates.\
  - % launches with all gate criteria updated in last 14 days.\
\
- Launch Quality:\
  - Count of Tier 1 launches slipping post-Go due to readiness issues.\
  - Qualitative feedback from PMs/PMMs/ELT.\
\
---\
\
## 10. Phasing\
\
### v1 (MVP \'96 operational)\
\
- Data model implemented.\
- Portfolio Dashboard, Launch Detail, My Items.\
- Readiness scoring + verdict.\
- Email reminders/alerts.\
- Aha sync (in + basic write-back).\
- Auth & RBAC.\
- Basic audit log.\
\
### v2+\
\
- Richer Aha write-back.\
- Slack integration.\
- T+30/T+90 post-launch tracking.\
- LLM-based summaries / exec briefs.\
- Advanced per-product / per-tier configuration.\
